meanings.definition: To surpass in class, quality, or skill.
meanings.sent1: The new student quickly outclassed his classmates in math.
meanings.sent2: The champion boxer easily outclassed his opponent in the ring.
meanings.sent3: The little squirrel outclassed the others by finding the biggest acorn.
meanings.sent4: Her beautiful singing voice outclassed all the other performers on stage.
meanings.sent5: The bright student outclassed everyone with his perfect score on the test.

meanings.definition: To be clearly superior to someone or something in a particular area.
meanings.sent1: The talented artist outclassed her peers with her stunning paintings.
meanings.sent2: The experienced team outclassed their rivals in the final match.
meanings.sent3: The clever cat outclassed the dog in catching the mouse.
meanings.sent4: The powerful storm outclassed all previous ones in its intensity.
meanings.sent5: The skilled dancer outclassed the others with her graceful movements.
